- Pedestrians are considered moving if their velocity in any direction (x, y, z) exceeds 0.5 units;
- The interaction distance is the distance between a pedestrian and an obstacle during a simulation time step;
- The simulation time is measured in seconds, and the frame rate is the number of frames per second in the simulation.

- 'pedestrian_id' refers to the unique identifier for each pedestrian in the simulation;
- 'time_step_id' represents the unique identifier for each time step in the simulation;
- 'distance_travelled' is the cumulative distance the pedestrian has traveled since the start of the simulation;
- 'velocity' (vx, vy) represents the speed and direction of the pedestrian at each time step;
- 'acceleration' (ax, ay) represents the change in velocity at each time step;
- 'interaction_type' indicates the type of interaction the pedestrian had with another pedestrian, if any.

sql:
